HEADWORD: Guiacol
<hw>Gui"a*col</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Guiac</ets> +
<ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless liquid,
<chform>C6H4.OCH3.OH</chform>, resembling the phenols, found as a
constituent of woodtar creosote, and produced by the dry distillation of
guaiac resin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

